## 3. Abstract Factory Pattern #2 — DAO Factory / Persistence Layer (All UCs)

### Problem
The project currently hard-codes SQL Server `DAO` instantiation everywhere:

```java
// In every controller constructor
private final AccountDAO accountDAO = new AccountDAO();
private final TransactionDAO transactionDAO = new TransactionDAO();
```

As new use cases are implemented, we add more DAOs (`LoanDAO`, `TransferDAO`, `InterestPostingDAO`, `OverdraftEventDAO`). These DAOs are **a family of related objects** — they all target the same database backend and use the same connection pool. If the project ever needs to support a different backend (e.g. PostgreSQL, or an in-memory store for testing), every controller must change.

This is the classic **Abstract Factory** for data access: define a `DAOFactory` interface and a concrete `SqlServerDAOFactory`.

### Design

```mermaid
classDiagram
    class DAOFactory {
        <<interface>>
        +createAccountDAO() AccountDAO
        +createCustomerDAO() CustomerDAO
        +createTransactionDAO() TransactionDAO
        +createLoanDAO() LoanDAO
        +createTransferDAO() TransferDAO
        +createInterestPostingDAO() InterestPostingDAO
        +createOverdraftEventDAO() OverdraftEventDAO
    }

    class SqlServerDAOFactory {
        +createAccountDAO() AccountDAO
        +createCustomerDAO() CustomerDAO
        +createTransactionDAO() TransactionDAO
        +createLoanDAO() LoanDAO
        +createTransferDAO() TransferDAO
        +createInterestPostingDAO() InterestPostingDAO
        +createOverdraftEventDAO() OverdraftEventDAO
    }

    class PersistenceManager {
        -DAOFactory factory$
        +getFactory() DAOFactory$
        +setFactory(DAOFactory factory)$
    }

    DAOFactory <|.. SqlServerDAOFactory
    PersistenceManager --> DAOFactory : holds
    SqlServerDAOFactory ..> AccountDAO : creates
    SqlServerDAOFactory ..> LoanDAO : creates
    SqlServerDAOFactory ..> TransferDAO : creates
```

### How it works

1. **`DAOFactory`** (new interface) declares a creation method for every DAO type in the system.

2. **`SqlServerDAOFactory`** (new class) implements it, returning the existing DAO classes that already use `DataSourceFactory` / HikariCP.

3. **`PersistenceManager`** (new class) acts as the global access point, holding a single `DAOFactory` instance:

```java
public class PersistenceManager {
    private static DAOFactory factory = new SqlServerDAOFactory();

    public static DAOFactory getFactory() { return factory; }
    public static void setFactory(DAOFactory f) { factory = f; }
}
```

4. **Controllers** stop hard-coding `new AccountDAO()` and instead call:

```java
public class DepositHandler extends TransactionController {
    private final AccountDAO accountDAO;
    private final TransactionDAO transactionDAO;

    public DepositHandler() {
        DAOFactory factory = PersistenceManager.getFactory();
        this.accountDAO = factory.createAccountDAO();
        this.transactionDAO = factory.createTransactionDAO();
    }
}
```

5. This is consumed by **every unimplemented use case** (UC-03 through UC-13) as they all need DAO instances.

### Files affected

| Action | File |
|--------|------|
| **[NEW]** | `persistence/DAOFactory.java` — abstract factory interface |
| **[NEW]** | `persistence/SqlServerDAOFactory.java` — concrete factory for SQL Server |
| **[NEW]** | `persistence/PersistenceManager.java` — singleton factory holder |
| **[MODIFY]** | All controllers (existing + new) — use `PersistenceManager.getFactory()` instead of `new XxxDAO()` |

---

## Summary Table

| # | Pattern | Where Applied | Use Cases Involved | New Classes |
|---|---------|--------------|-------------------|-------------|
| 1 | **Factory Method** | `TransactionController.createTransaction()` | UC-05, UC-06, UC-07 | 1 abstract class |
| 2 | **Abstract Factory** | `LoanFactory` (Validator + Calculator + Loan) | UC-09, UC-10, UC-11 | 1 interface + 2 product interfaces + 3 concrete factories |
| 3 | **Abstract Factory** | `DAOFactory` (all DAOs) | All UCs (UC-03 – UC-13) | 1 interface + 1 concrete factory + 1 manager |
